<div id="review_1427732517" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1427732517" />
    <a title="Michael Sump" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3050876-michael-sump"><img alt="Michael Sump" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1497070786p2/3050876.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1427732517?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Sump" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Sump" href="/user/show/3050876-michael-sump">Michael Sump</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1427732517" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10757932529622835065">A Jewish perspective on the Arab experience from the 1920s to the birth of Israel in the form of a novel. A clear indictment of Arab inhumanity to the Palestinian people. Leon Uris, who is Jewish, is not without bias. However, it seems to me, that he largely tells the true story of a people, the Palestinians, who have been failed again and again by their leaders and by their Arab brothers. A key event of this story has recently been in the news as Netanyahu tried to put the blame of the holocaus</span>
  <span id="freeText10757932529622835065" style="display:none">A Jewish perspective on the Arab experience from the 1920s to the birth of Israel in the form of a novel. A clear indictment of Arab inhumanity to the Palestinian people. Leon Uris, who is Jewish, is not without bias. However, it seems to me, that he largely tells the true story of a people, the Palestinians, who have been failed again and again by their leaders and by their Arab brothers. A key event of this story has recently been in the news as Netanyahu tried to put the blame of the holocaust on a pre-WWII Palestinian leader. This is nonsense, but there is no question that the Arabs were eager to side with Germany and to participate in the annihilation of Jews, but clearly the idea of this crime did not originate in the Middle East. It is a sad story but one that is interesting and well worth reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10757932529622835065" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


